<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="High_availability_considerations">High availability considerations</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DepModOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: High availability considerations">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DepModOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: High availability considerations">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The suite supports both single-master and multiple-master deployment.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Multi-master_deployment">Multi-master deployment</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DepModOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Multi-master deployment">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DepModOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Multi-master deployment">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The suite is deployed in 2 or 3 Availability Zones (AZs). This option is mainly for production purpose.
</p>
<ul><li>All the components are designed for high availability. The master and worker nodes are distributed across multiple AZs. Amazon Elastic File System (EFS) is used as highly available storage by default. Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS) can be easily configured for high availability across multiple AZs.</li>
<li>The architecture is designed for the network architecture that meets higher security standard such as DMZ.
<ul><li>All the CDF and Operations Bridge related components are located in private subnet. No direct access allowed.</li>
<li>Cloud Management Platform (CMP) and Marketplace Portal (MPP) users can only connect to the specified ports (for example: 8444 and 8089) for business purposes.</li>
<li>Administrators can connect to the bastion nodes in public subnets and then jump to the private network for cluster management. Only a limited number of users can access the bastion nodes.</li></ul></li>
<li>The architecture also considers performance balance against availability. The master and worker nodes are distributed across multiple AZs instead of regions, which makes sure the network latency between different AZs is less than 1 millisecond in most cases, and guarantees minor performance penalty introduced by latency.</li></ul>
<p><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="SMA-X on AWS 2018.05 multi AZ 0.2.png" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/81/SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_multi_AZ_0.2.png/800px-SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_multi_AZ_0.2.png" width="800" height="1038" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/81/SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_multi_AZ_0.2.png/1200px-SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_multi_AZ_0.2.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/8/81/SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_multi_AZ_0.2.png 2x" data-file-width="1575" data-file-height="2044"></a>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Single-master_deployment">Single-master deployment</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DepModOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=3" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Single-master deployment">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DepModOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Single-master deployment">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The suite is deployed in 1 AZ. This deployment is mainly for demo, development, performance evaluation, and other non-production purposes.
</p><p><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="SMA-X on AWS 2018.05 single AZ 0.2.png" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/b/bb/SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_single_AZ_0.2.png/800px-SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_single_AZ_0.2.png" width="800" height="837" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/b/bb/SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_single_AZ_0.2.png/1200px-SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_single_AZ_0.2.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/b/bb/SMA-X_on_AWS_2018.05_single_AZ_0.2.png 2x" data-file-width="1251" data-file-height="1309"></a>
</p>
